A 1976 dream and prediction included in an intriguing bio titled 'Saved By The Buddha Within', sums up the virus and what's still to come and leaves it up to the reader to decide if it is something that has escaped from a lab or something that has been deliberately placed here to reduce the population possibly by an alien force... 'It was during one of my under-the-covers writing sessions, that I drifted off and had yet another mysterious dream. I was floating very close behind the tail of a jet airliner as it was taking off, and being gently bombarded by masses of specks that looked like translucent particles churning out of the engines as they propelled the plane into the air. It felt so real that it still seems like it actually happened. Next, I was watching a helicopter flying by – only instead of pushing, it was pulling itself along – the blades were acting like arms swimming through the same tiny particles. After the plane and helicopter had faded into the distance, a flying saucer crossed my mind – I wondered how they might function. In the next instant, one was sitting in a field right in front of me. It was made up of two silver saucer-shaped discs that fitted perfectly together face to face. While one of the discs spun clockwise, the other spun anti-clockwise, and there were three large holes in the inner walls where the discs met and joined. I somehow understood that the energy being generated and released from the holes in one disc was simultaneously being absorbed magnetically and utilised by the holes in the other disc, as a self-perpetuating power source. I can’t recall seeing any windows, but when I moved closer, I was surprised to discover that it wasn’t silver at all – it was a rusty-reddish colour, and on its upper surface were thousands of grooves around its circumference – similar to a vinyl record.

In the next instant, I was inside observing a large circular recess in the craft’s centre – the walls appeared to be similar to aluminium or stainless steel, with hieroglyphic symbols and what appeared to be touch-control pads next to them. As I continued to observe, a message was conveyed to me from within or around me – I’m not sure, stating that the technology was capable of producing gravity and a balanced artificial environment that could be maintained regardless of speed or direction. I wondered what the source of this power could be, and the immediate answer that came to me was neutron energy. I awoke to wonder what on earth a ‘cosmic neutron’ was. I had no idea, so I hurried upstairs and asked Jean if she could shed any light on it. While we both understood what cosmic meant, she had no idea what a neutron was either, so she went to a box and pulled out an old English dictionary that she’d inherited and kept for many years, in the hope that it would one day become valuable. Flicking through the pages, Jean found information that puzzled and amazed us both. The dictionary stated that a neutron was a form of cosmic energy that some scientists believed existed but hadn’t at that point been able to identify – it was probably a similar situation back then to the present day mystery regarding Dark Matter. Lost in a maze of thoughts about my dream, I returned to my flat and my trusty heater to try to get warm up again and soon fell off to sleep.

While I was doodling a few days later, I found myself jotting several odd things down on a pad as random thoughts popped in and out of my mind. I eventually fell off to sleep on the sofa and didn’t wake up until sometime later – pen still in my hand. When I read what I’d written, I couldn’t believe I’d done it – some of what I wrote not only scared the wits out of me but made me feel nauseous. In my notes, I’d described YouTube to a ‘T’ – secret bases on the Moon that belonged to the US, China and Europe, and dark, negative things that I’d never seen or thought about before – gloomy and terrifying predictions for the future of the world and its inhabitants. My notes stated that humankind would eventually be able to transfer people’s brainwaves onto a screen – view their thoughts and expose their hidden secrets – including their transition from life to death and beyond. My ‘jottings’ also revealed that, in the future, if people became incurably ill or too old and costly to maintain or were unable to look after themselves, they’d be instantly terminated by way of electromagnetic technology. In other words, atoms that make up the body, or anything else physical, would be instantly dissembled at the flick of a switch, so to speak, and end up a pile of fine dust. Although some cancers and other 20th century ailments would be curable, worse diseases would arise and take their place. One such disease would destroy all living body cells within a matter of days, resulting in agonising death. Another future global pandemic would cause bleeding from the eyes, mouth and ears, while the body rapidly degenerated within a matter of hours. I’d also written about far worse diseases brought about by human-induced neutron energy exposure, and how they’d spread like wildfire – but without any detailed explanations as to what they would be. There were the usual predictions of ever-increasing record-breaking earthquakes – droughts – floods – cyclones – fires – killer tornados – and warnings that some of the disasters would destroy whole cities and leave the land barren and reduced to waste. It appeared to be that a lot of these events would be brought about through the direct effects or side-effects of neutron energy.

Prompted by some of what I’d written, I proceeded to write a fictitious short story about a French-made ‘neutron aircraft’ going out of control and crashing in India, with catastrophic results. The ‘saucer-shaped’ craft had been designed by way of reverse engineering after an abandoned alien spacecraft was found in the jungle somewhere near New Guinea. The initial explosion of the French copy triggered off an ongoing neutron storm that turned everything in its path to dust. The earth’s magnetic field and gravitational pull became so severely damaged that everything in the storm’s path – living – inanimate – water and air, was dragged into outer space from the earth’s crust. Eventually, the surfaces of the land were left grey and barren – similar to the surface of the moon. Avoiding the worst of the upheaval, several of the world’s elites, including renowned scientists – doctors – politicians and other influential leaders – most of whom were fully or partially responsible for the destructive outcome, manage to escape to the moon, using a neutron-powered spacecraft. Soon afterwards, they move onward to a planet resembling Earth that had previously been discovered but had never been physically visited. During their long and tedious journey to reach it, they watched some of the video clips that they’d previously chosen to ignore, made by citizens concerned about the dangerous situation that the world was in. Although YouTube still hadn’t been invented, the presentations of my visions of the future in my story described it to a ‘T’. In the end, I put it all down to my imagination, but deep inside, I had an overbearing feeling that if the ailing situation in the world didn’t improve quickly, especially where people’s attitudes are concerned, it could one day come to pass.

Since that time, several new dangerous viruses have arisen in the world, including AIDS and another one that clearly matches some of my fictitious story named Ebola. I now believe that some dreams are like presents that keep us wondering until we open them to reveal what’s inside. In other words, the hidden underlying message sometimes doesn’t become apparent until it becomes a reality. I’ve more recently wondered if my dream and story may have been related to CERN or something similar.
